cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of detecting out-of-distribution samples in deep learning models, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new evaluation scheme, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
